          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A Li-7 implanted into Al target with (6.6+-0.4)E+17",
                "Li-7/cm**2 was used for the measurement of angular",
                "distributions for Li-7(p,a).",
                "Excitation functions for both Li reactions were",
                "measured with three targets- two LiF targets-",
                " (6.1+-0.2)*E+17 Li-7/cm**2 and (9.0+-0.4)*E+17 Li-7/",
                " cm**2- vacuum-evaporated on Ag and Cu backing( Li of",
                " natural isotopic composition-92.58% Li-7, 7.42% Li-6)",
                " and the Li-7 implanted into Al target, which were",
                " positioned inside the target chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The beam current on target was kept below",
                " 200 nA."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.The effective energy E within the target",
                "was derived from the incident energy of the ion beam",
                "and the energy loss of the beam in the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ". The quoted uncertainties for S(E) arise from",
                "uncertainty in the number of incident protons, measured",
                "by a charge integrator and was obtained as 4%.",
                "The statistical uncertainty associated with N(E(o),ang-",
                "lab)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".A 5% uncertainty in stopping cross sections",
                " affects not only S(E) but also the effective energy.",
                " However, simulations show that the 5% uncertainty",
                " propagates into very small variations in energy-",
                " less 0.5% and in S(E) less 3.7%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
